<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Architecture Decision Records on Zaba505's Home Lab</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/</link><description>Recent content in Architecture Decision Records on Zaba505's Home Lab</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[0001] Public/Private Infrastructure Split</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../_index.md"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-27-span-public-cloud-and-privatehome-lab-infrastructure-with-the-connectivity-between-them-part-of-the-foundation"&gt;TR-27&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-01-provide-compute-as-a-tenant-offering"&gt;TR-01&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-02-provide-persistent-storage-as-a-tenant-offering"&gt;TR-02&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-03-provide-network-reachability--internal-between-tenants-and-external-for-end-users"&gt;TR-03&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-05-provide-backup-and-disaster-recovery-of-tenant-data"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-17-definitions-driven-single-entry-point-rebuild-of-the-platform-end-to-end"&gt;TR-17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-22-tracked-changes-and-immutability-for-all-platform-state-modifying-actions"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-32-per-tenant-authentication-and-isolation-strong-enough-that-no-tenant-or-its-capability-owner-via-the-observability-offering-can-read-another-tenants-data-or-signals"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-33-routine-platform-operation-must-fit-within-2-hoursweek-of-operator-time"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context-and-problem-statement"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-27-span-public-cloud-and-privatehome-lab-infrastructure-with-the-connectivity-between-them-part-of-the-foundation"&gt;TR-27&lt;/a&gt; forces the platform to span public-cloud and private/home-lab infrastructure, with the connectivity between them part of the foundation. The capability rule that grounds this — &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;self-hosted means the operator controls end-to-end, not that every component runs on hardware the operator owns&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; — leaves the &lt;em&gt;split&lt;/em&gt; unspecified: any of the platform&amp;rsquo;s offerings (TR-01 compute, TR-02 storage, TR-03 reachability, TR-04 identity, TR-05 backup, TR-06 observability) may be placed on either side.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0002] Compute Substrate</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../_index.md"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-01-provide-compute-as-a-tenant-offering"&gt;TR-01&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-12-provide-a-one-shot-migration-process-offering-that-runs-tenant-supplied-migration-jobs"&gt;TR-12&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-13-admit-migration-jobs-only-when-their-peak-temporary-footprint-is-at-most-2-the-destination-tenants-steady-state-compute-and-storage"&gt;TR-13&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-17-definitions-driven-single-entry-point-rebuild-of-the-platform-end-to-end"&gt;TR-17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-19-each-rebuild-phase-must-be-cleanly-torn-downable-the-partial-state-is-itself-untrusted"&gt;TR-19&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-20-maintain-a-purpose-built-canary-tenant-alongside-the-platforms-definitions-and-use-it-as-the-readiness-signal"&gt;TR-20&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-22-tracked-changes-and-immutability-for-all-platform-state-modifying-actions"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-24-tenant-provisioning-must-run-only-through-the-platforms-existing-definitions"&gt;TR-24&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-25-during-platform-contract-change-rollouts-run-old-and-new-forms-of-the-offering-concurrently-until-the-deadline-except-where-the-change-is-a-full-removal"&gt;TR-25&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-26-tenants-declare-resource-needs-at-onboarding-and-on-every-modify-the-platform-admits-or-refuses-based-on-those-declarations"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-32-per-tenant-authentication-and-isolation-strong-enough-that-no-tenant-or-its-capability-owner-via-the-observability-offering-can-read-another-tenants-data-or-signals"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-33-routine-platform-operation-must-fit-within-2-hoursweek-of-operator-time"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context-and-problem-statement"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./0001-public-private-infrastructure-split.md"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; places tenant compute on the home-lab side. This ADR picks the substrate that actually runs tenant workloads there. It is the single biggest downstream constraint in this design: it dictates what tenant packaging form is plausible (ADR #3), how the migration runner is built (ADR #10), what observability and identity hooks are available (ADRs #5, #8), and how per-tenant isolation (TR-32) is enforced.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0003] Tenant Packaging Form</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../_index.md"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-10-provide-a-packaging-form-the-platform-accepts-for-all-tenant-components"&gt;TR-10&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-11-provide-a-secret-management-offering-tenants-can-register-secrets-with-and-reference-by-name"&gt;TR-11&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-12-provide-a-one-shot-migration-process-offering-that-runs-tenant-supplied-migration-jobs"&gt;TR-12&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-22-tracked-changes-and-immutability-for-all-platform-state-modifying-actions"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-24-tenant-provisioning-must-run-only-through-the-platforms-existing-definitions"&gt;TR-24&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-26-tenants-declare-resource-needs-at-onboarding-and-on-every-modify-the-platform-admits-or-refuses-based-on-those-declarations"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-31-migration-jobs-declare-a-re-run-contract-that-the-platform-records-and-respects"&gt;TR-31&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-32-per-tenant-authentication-and-isolation-strong-enough-that-no-tenant-or-its-capability-owner-via-the-observability-offering-can-read-another-tenants-data-or-signals"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context-and-problem-statement"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./0002-compute-substrate.md"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; chose Kubernetes as the compute substrate. That constrains but does not fully decide the tenant packaging form: K8s can accept anything from &amp;ldquo;an OCI image and we&amp;rsquo;ll write the manifests for you&amp;rdquo; to &amp;ldquo;a full Helm chart&amp;rdquo; to &amp;ldquo;raw Deployment YAML.&amp;rdquo; TR-10 demands one accepted form for tenant components, and that same form must be acceptable for migration-process artifacts (TR-12).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0004] Persistent Storage Offering — Block as the Foundational Primitive</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0004-persistent-storage-offering/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0004-persistent-storage-offering/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../_index.md"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-02-provide-persistent-storage-as-a-tenant-offering"&gt;TR-02&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-05-provide-backup-and-disaster-recovery-of-tenant-data"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-15-support-tenant-lifecycle-stage-live--eviction-frozen-computenetwork-deprovisioned-data-read-only--tenant-accessible-copy-removed-at-30-days"&gt;TR-15&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-32-per-tenant-authentication-and-isolation-strong-enough-that-no-tenant-or-its-capability-owner-via-the-observability-offering-can-read-another-tenants-data-or-signals"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-33-routine-platform-operation-must-fit-within-2-hoursweek-of-operator-time"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context-and-problem-statement"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./0001-public-private-infrastructure-split.md"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; places bulk persistent storage on the home-lab side. &lt;a href="./0002-compute-substrate.md"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; chose Kubernetes. This ADR decides what persistent-storage &lt;em&gt;offerings&lt;/em&gt; the platform exposes to tenants and how the eviction-frozen state from &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-15-support-tenant-lifecycle-stage-live--eviction-frozen-computenetwork-deprovisioned-data-read-only--tenant-accessible-copy-removed-at-30-days"&gt;TR-15&lt;/a&gt; works against them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is real tension to resolve here. On one side, tenants will need different shapes of storage over time — object stores for media, relational DBs for transactional data, possibly graph or time-series later. On the other side, the parent capability&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;evolves with its tenants&lt;/em&gt; rule says the platform should grow when tenants need it, not before. Adding three managed offerings up front, ahead of any tenant who needs them, fails that rule by going ahead of the tenants and inflates &lt;a href="../tech-requirements.md#tr-33-routine-platform-operation-must-fit-within-2-hoursweek-of-operator-time"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt; routine maintenance for offerings nobody yet uses.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>